00:43:21.380 --> 00:43:24.175
So please make a line
and ask questions.

00:43:24.175 --> 00:43:26.190
AUDIENCE: We also have
Mike setting up the mic.

00:43:26.190 --> 00:43:28.640
SOPHIE EGAN: Mike
setting up the mic.

00:43:28.640 --> 00:43:31.440
AUDIENCE: In the
blurb for your talk,

00:43:31.440 --> 00:43:34.880
one of the things
that was mentioned

00:43:34.880 --> 00:43:37.640
was gluten free,
which made me think

00:43:37.640 --> 00:43:41.020
it seems to me that
there's been an explosion

00:43:41.020 --> 00:43:47.160
over the last couple of decades
of people self-diagnosing food

00:43:47.160 --> 00:43:49.880
restrictions.

00:43:49.880 --> 00:43:51.380
The gluten-free
thing is probably

00:43:51.380 --> 00:43:55.540
the most extreme where there
is this actual condition called

00:43:55.540 --> 00:44:03.310
celiac disease, and people who
have it can't deal with gluten.

00:44:03.310 --> 00:44:06.810
But there's 10 or 100
times as many people

00:44:06.810 --> 00:44:12.320
as have celiac disease that have
decided by themselves, largely,

00:44:12.320 --> 00:44:14.590
without the aid of
medical professionals,

00:44:14.590 --> 00:44:17.460
that they're gluten sensitive.

00:44:17.460 --> 00:44:23.302
And you see the same thing with
people deciding on their own

00:44:23.302 --> 00:44:26.450
they're lactose intolerant
or various other things.

00:44:26.450 --> 00:44:29.630
I wondered what you make
of this and why we seem

00:44:29.630 --> 00:44:31.590
to be overwhelmed by this now.

00:44:31.590 --> 00:44:32.490
SOPHIE EGAN: Yeah.

00:44:32.490 --> 00:44:33.240
Thank you for the question.

00:44:33.240 --> 00:44:34.156
It's a great question.

00:44:34.156 --> 00:44:35.480
It comes up a lot.

00:44:35.480 --> 00:44:37.210
I actually have a
piece coming out

00:44:37.210 --> 00:44:39.610
very soon about this very
topic because I've been asked

00:44:39.610 --> 00:44:42.120
about it a number of times.

00:44:42.120 --> 00:44:45.040
There definitely is a lot
of self-diagnosis going on.

00:44:45.040 --> 00:44:48.030
The numbers, you're very close.

00:44:48.030 --> 00:44:52.675
It's about 1% of people have
celiac disease, very severe

00:44:52.675 --> 00:44:57.770
autoimmune condition that
damages the small intestine.

00:44:57.770 --> 00:45:02.340
About roughly 7%-- though
they really don't know--

00:45:02.340 --> 00:45:06.200
appear to have non-celiac
gluten sensitivity.

00:45:06.200 --> 00:45:10.080
Fully a third of Americans
are trying to avoid gluten.

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:12.727
And that really speaks
to what you're saying,

00:45:12.727 --> 00:45:14.810
I think, in terms of this
getting really blown out

00:45:14.810 --> 00:45:15.642
of proportion.

00:45:15.642 --> 00:45:17.100
The other concern
I have is that it

00:45:17.100 --> 00:45:21.000
is miss-- it's kind of
like misappropriating

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:23.279
the real cause of gluten free.

00:45:23.279 --> 00:45:24.820
Because the real
cause of gluten free

00:45:24.820 --> 00:45:26.270
is that this is a real sickness.

00:45:26.270 --> 00:45:28.250
And most people now
in the wake of a lot

00:45:28.250 --> 00:45:31.940
of these different diet
books and the whole segment

00:45:31.940 --> 00:45:34.990
of the grocery store
that's been opened up,

00:45:34.990 --> 00:45:36.750
it's become about weight loss.

00:45:36.750 --> 00:45:40.760
And if I eat gluten
free, then I won't

00:45:40.760 --> 00:45:41.960
have these stomach problems.

00:45:41.960 --> 00:45:43.250
And I'll lose
weight, and I'll have

00:45:43.250 --> 00:45:45.041
more energy and all of
the different things

00:45:45.041 --> 00:45:46.370
that are associated with that.

00:45:46.370 --> 00:45:49.890
There is not scientific
data to support the idea

00:45:49.890 --> 00:45:53.280
that gluten-free diet
makes you lose weight.

00:45:53.280 --> 00:45:57.520
And the way that I
interpret what's going on

00:45:57.520 --> 00:45:59.960
is a couple of things.

00:45:59.960 --> 00:46:01.630
First to the
self-diagnosis point,

00:46:01.630 --> 00:46:05.600
I see a lot of that
with-- what does

00:46:05.600 --> 00:46:07.700
really going on a
gluten-free diet mean to you?

00:46:07.700 --> 00:46:10.366
If you are all of a sudden more
conscious in general of what

00:46:10.366 --> 00:46:12.240
you're eating because
you're checking labels,

00:46:12.240 --> 00:46:16.370
maybe you're slowing
down, maybe you're

00:46:16.370 --> 00:46:18.950
checking the portion size
or things that you before

00:46:18.950 --> 00:46:21.450
didn't give another thought
to-- there's definitely actually

00:46:21.450 --> 00:46:25.020
some science that shows that
the people have better results

00:46:25.020 --> 00:46:27.527
merely when they're paying
more attention to whatever

00:46:27.527 --> 00:46:28.610
it is that they're eating.

00:46:28.610 --> 00:46:30.590
Second is that if
going gluten free

00:46:30.590 --> 00:46:32.560
means you're eating less
cookies and less chips

00:46:32.560 --> 00:46:34.090
and you're drinking less
beer and you're also

00:46:34.090 --> 00:46:35.840
eating healthier things,
then you probably

00:46:35.840 --> 00:46:38.300
feel like a million bucks.

00:46:38.300 --> 00:46:43.450
And a lot of people do
report some of these results

00:46:43.450 --> 00:46:46.146
and miss-attribute
it to the gluten.

00:46:46.146 --> 00:46:47.520
I'm not saying
all the people who

00:46:47.520 --> 00:46:52.250
feel that way don't have
non-celiac gluten sensitivity.

00:46:52.250 --> 00:46:54.890
But it's a real murky
area, particularly

00:46:54.890 --> 00:46:59.130
with that one, the non-celiac
gluten sensitivity.

00:46:59.130 --> 00:47:01.000
Not that much is
known about it yet.

00:47:01.000 --> 00:47:02.990
And there isn't really
a way to test for it.

00:47:02.990 --> 00:47:04.406
But I did find it
very interesting

00:47:04.406 --> 00:47:07.150
that Celiac Disease
Foundation actually

00:47:07.150 --> 00:47:09.670
is pretty clear on their
website about this.

00:47:09.670 --> 00:47:12.530
They say do not self-diagnose.

00:47:12.530 --> 00:47:16.180
Please consult with
your doctor before going

00:47:16.180 --> 00:47:17.310
on a gluten-free diet.

00:47:17.310 --> 00:47:20.890
And that seems to be a message
that's getting overlooked.

00:47:20.890 --> 00:47:23.940
A lot of people are OK, now
I'm gluten free for life

00:47:23.940 --> 00:47:26.300
or whatever it is.

00:47:26.300 --> 00:47:28.820
And a lot of it also spreads
from one person to the next.

00:47:28.820 --> 00:47:30.480
I describe in the
book this phenomenon

00:47:30.480 --> 00:47:32.700
that gluten free is not
the first example of this,

00:47:32.700 --> 00:47:38.690
but there's this diet
evangelism, a kind of "join me"

00:47:38.690 --> 00:47:41.570
mentality of whatever
it is that you're part.

00:47:41.570 --> 00:47:45.619
And it doesn't mean, again, that
some of the people genuinely

00:47:45.619 --> 00:47:46.910
really need to be on that diet.

00:47:46.910 --> 00:47:49.800
But for the proportion
of the population that's

00:47:49.800 --> 00:47:53.990
paying attention to it,
it's just the latest example

00:47:53.990 --> 00:47:56.670
what I describe also in
the book as selling absent.

00:47:56.670 --> 00:47:59.440
It's valuing foods
based on what they lack.

00:47:59.440 --> 00:48:01.580
And we saw this with fat free.

00:48:01.580 --> 00:48:04.050
And what happens, unfortunately,
is that all these products

00:48:04.050 --> 00:48:05.830
get reformulated.

00:48:05.830 --> 00:48:08.600
And you have to replace
the gluten with something.

00:48:08.600 --> 00:48:11.090
So do you ever look
at the ingredient list

00:48:11.090 --> 00:48:12.796
of a lot of
gluten-free products?

00:48:12.796 --> 00:48:13.670
They're excruciating.

00:48:13.670 --> 00:48:16.580
And they have all kinds of
potato starch and tapioca

00:48:16.580 --> 00:48:20.140
powder and whatnot that are not
any better, and in some cases,

00:48:20.140 --> 00:48:22.870
are actually worse than
the original product.

00:48:22.870 --> 00:48:24.870
And again, this
happened with fat free.

00:48:24.870 --> 00:48:28.210
So it really depends.

00:48:28.210 --> 00:48:30.230
I think people
have been surprised

00:48:30.230 --> 00:48:34.280
how long this trend has lasted.

00:48:34.280 --> 00:48:35.730
Part of it is that
a lot is still

00:48:35.730 --> 00:48:37.577
unknown about digestive health.

00:48:37.577 --> 00:48:39.910
Gut health in general is
becoming a much more mainstream

00:48:39.910 --> 00:48:42.090
topic.

00:48:42.090 --> 00:48:46.740
Self-diagnosis and then
also just that more products

00:48:46.740 --> 00:48:48.210
are available than ever before.

00:48:48.210 --> 00:48:50.620
And the market always
responds to these things.

00:48:50.620 --> 00:48:54.810
So we have to, I hope, keep
a little bit of a level

00:48:54.810 --> 00:48:57.960
head for those of us--
I, personally, do not

00:48:57.960 --> 00:49:05.379
have sensitivity to gluten, so
I think we need to keep a level

00:49:05.379 --> 00:49:06.420
head about a lot of this.

00:49:09.634 --> 00:49:10.300
PETE: Thank you.

